# Deployment Plan - GitHub and Vercel

This plan details the steps to publish the **Avani Loan Agents** project to a public GitHub repository and deploy it to Vercel.

---

## User Review Required

> [!WARNING]
> **API Credentials & Database Persistence on Vercel**
> 1. **Security**: We will create a `.gitignore` file to ensure that `.env.local` (containing API keys) and local databases (`database.db`) are **never** pushed to public GitHub.
> 2. **Environment Variables**: For the AI Chat and integrations to work on the live Vercel URL, you will need to add `GEMINI_API_KEY` and other integration keys in the Vercel Project Dashboard.
> 3. **SQLite Ephemerality**: Vercel runs on a serverless, read-only ephemeral file system. This means writing to `database.db` on Vercel will fail or reset on every cold start. The website will successfully run, but production leads will be sent to your active integrations (HubSpot, Google Sheets, Make, Pabbly) and not saved persistently in SQLite on Vercel.

