## Proposed Changes

### Component 1: Git & Repository Setup

#### [NEW] [.gitignore](file:///c:/Users/ALPHA-1/Desktop/AVANI%20LOAN%20AGENTS/.gitignore)
Create a standard Next.js `.gitignore` file to prevent committing dependency folders (`node_modules`), build output (`.next`), local environment secrets (`.env.local`), and SQLite files (`*.db`).

#### Git Initial Commit
We will initialize the git repository and commit the clean codebase:
```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit - Avani Loan Agents"
```

#### GitHub Repo Creation
Using the pre-authenticated GitHub CLI (`gh`), we will create a public repository and push the code:
```bash
gh repo create avani-loan-agents --public --source=. --remote=origin --push
```

---

### Component 2: Vercel Deployment

We will link and deploy the project to Vercel:
```bash
vercel --confirm
```

